content: Spicy fish and coconut dish **Fish moilee**/**moily** or **fish molee** (**meen molee**) is a spicy [fish](/wiki/Fish_as_food) and [coconut](/wiki/Coconut) dish of possible Portuguese or Indian origin. It is common in [India](/wiki/India), [Malaysia](/wiki/Malaysia) and [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore). During the times of the [British Empire](/wiki/British_Empire), it spread into other places of [South-East Asia](/wiki/South-East_Asia), such as [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore). The name may be associated with a kind of [curry](/wiki/Curry) known among [Malayali](/wiki/Malayali) of Southern India as Moli. - Fish Molee recipe This [Indian cuisine](/wiki/Indian_cuisine)â€“related article is a stub.
